Suppose the masses $m_1, m_2, m_3, m_4$ are located at positions $x_1, x_2, x_3, x_4$ in a line and connected by springs with spring constants $k_{12}, k_{23}, k _{34}$ whose natural lengths are $\ell_{12}, \ell_{23}, \ell_{34}$.
Let $f_1, f_2, f_3, f_4$ denote the rightward forces located on the masses, i.e. $f_1 = k_{12} (x_2 - x_1 - \ell_{12})$.
	\begin{figure}[h]
